As part of strategy to address water scarcity and improve water sanitation and hygiene (WASH), at the grassroots, Sen Binos Yaroe  (Adamawa- PDP Southern), has inaugurated  five solar powered boreholes in different communities in his constituency. The lawmaker, over the weekend inaugurated the projects in Bille, Green Village, Wuro Abba and Jada towns  across Numan, Jada and Demsa councils as part of his campaign promises to the people. He said provision of portable water to his constituents was deliberate to avert cholera, diarrhoea, ammoebiasis and other water borne disease, identified  with drinking   contaminated  water. The lawmaker listed  some of the projects  executed to mark his first anniversary in office to  includes medical outreach to 13,000 parents, training of youths on leadership  entrepreneurship and skill development, distribution of relief materials to flood and conflict victims. Yaroe vowed to concentrated on 4 key area on  health, water, education and youth empowerments as fulfilment to better the lots of his people. The District  Head  of Wurro-abbo in Jada local government Mahmud Ardo lauded the lawmaker  for fulfilling his promises to his  people and sought further intervention in the area of agriculture and improved security of lives and people in  the area. The  paramount traditional ruler of Batta kingdom, Hama Batta Chief. Alhamdu Teneke, who received the Senator at his place in Demsa appealed to the  elected representatives in the area to facilitate the completion of the on-going constructions of  Numan -jalingo road. The Royal father who  lamented  that, the road project  awarded in the last three years by the federal government is yet to be completed,  exposing commuters and motorists to untold hardship especially during the rainy season. 